page.title: 02Landscape
page.content: The landscape is generally hilly. There are also lots of woodland. The main land use is for farming. There are three quarries in the area but none are now in use. There are six springs and one reservoire. Most of the land is{four hundred {feet}above sea level and at is highest is{five hundred and twenty five feet above sea level.there are two wells and one lake in our area. There are two rivers in our area called Oddford Brook and the River Nadder. The farm land is used to grow corn and potatoes and vines.
